physical_examinations.relevant_findings: The patient presented with perineal hypospadias, micropenis, and a bifid scrotum containing gonads. Penile length was 5 cm, testis volumes were 6 ml bilaterally at age 15, and he developed bilateral gynecomastia (stage 4). Basal LH was 15.7 IU/liter, peak LH was 68.8 IU/liter; basal FSH was 15.5 IU/liter, peak FSH was 34.7 IU/liter; basal testosterone was 9.6 nmol/liter, peak testosterone was 32.3 nmol/liter. Final height was 172.5 cm (25th centile).
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Testis volumes increased to 10 ml by 20 years of age, but no further virilization was noted.
